This paper deals with joint decoding of distributed source-channel (DSC) coded systems, which involves information theory (IT) and networking (NI) concepts. The use of low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes is a common technique in coding theory and falls under the category of signal processing (SI). The paper also deals with exploiting temporal and source correlations, which is a topic in data science (DS) and machine learning (MM). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT, followed by cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, and cs.MM.
